[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:
-----------------------------------------
The Americas region reported 50.7% of the global newly reported cases and 53.0% of newly reported fatalities for this 24-hour period. The USA reported 36.2% of the newly confirmed cases in the region, Brazil reported 28.5%, Chile 8.6%, Peru 7.7%, and Mexico 6.9%. The same 5 countries at the top.

The European region reported 14.6% of the global newly reported cases and 13.2% of the newly confirmed cases in the region, Russia reported 47.8% of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Turkey 9.2%, the UK 5.6%, Sweden 4.5%, Belarus 4.1%, and Ukraine 3.9%. Again, same countries, minor juggling of orders and percentages on a daily basis.

The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 15.7% of the global newly reported cases and 14.8% of global newly reported fatalities. Saudi Arabia reported 24.3% of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Pakistan 23.9%, Iran 13.2%, Egypt 9.1%, Qatar 6.9%, Iraq 6.0%, and Oman 5.6%.

The African region reported 5.4% of the global newly reported cases and 3.8% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 54.6% of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Nigeria 9.0%, Gabon 8.9%, Ghana 8.5%, Cameroon 4.6%, and Ethiopia 2.8%. While South Africa and Nigeria are consistently number 1 and number 2 in terms of 24 hour increase in cases, other countries have less consistent reporting patterns and vary considerably from day to day.

The Western Pacific region reported 0.78% of the global newly reported cases and 0.40% of global fatalities. The Philippines reported 52.9% of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Singapore 23.1%, Japan 9.2%, and China 4.9%. The outbreak associated with the Beijing Seafood markets has brought China to prominence in terms of daily newly confirmed cases.

The South East Asia region reported 12.9% of the global newly reported cases and 14.8% of global fatalities. India reported 69.8% of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 20.3%, Indonesia 6.7%, and Nepal 3.0%. Same countries, same order as in previous days.

Impression: Europe seems to be stabilizing at a significantly lower rate, although Russia is still reporting 8000+ new cases a day. The Eastern Mediterranean has surpassed the European region with Pakistan reporting 5-6000+ cases a day. South East Asia is approaching parity with the European and Eastern Mediterranean regions with India reporting 8000-10 000+ cases a day. The Eastern Mediterranean region has surpassed the European region for the past 2 days in terms of newly confirmed cases. The Americas region is reporting around 70 000 cases a day with Brazil usually reporting 25 000-30 000+ cases a day (today16 Jun 2020, was only 17 110 cases), and the USA seems to have stabilized at 20 000+ a day. In the Africa region, the regional proportion is slowly climbing, with South Africa reporting in the 2000-3000+ range daily, and in the Western Pacific region, they are maintaining a very low rate compared with the other regions, with the Philippines averaging 400+ cases per day (Singapore had been reporting twice as many cases per day for a period of time but has dropped back over the past couple of weeks).

Figure 3. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases, by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 16 Jun 2020, at the source URL above, is an excellent representation of the epidemic starting in the Western Pacific, transitioning to multiregional activity as the virus travelled. Europe has significantly decreased. The Americas region continues to increase, as does South East Asia, which is approaching parity with the European region in terms of daily newly confirmed cases and the Eastern Mediterranean, which has overtaken the European region; the African region is noticeably increasing as well. The Americas region continues to greatly outnumber all other regions for daily reporting. - Mod.MPP]

